Marc-Andre ter Stegen played a crucial part in Barcelona's victory against Manchester City as he thwarted Sergio Aguero's 78th-minute penalty effort, but it looks like the Barca goalkeeper has one of his team-mates to thank for his spot-kick heroics. 

Trailing 1-0 on the night, and 3-1 on aggregate, City were handed a lifeline when Aguero was tripped by Gerard Pique in the penalty area.  

Referee Gianluca Rocchi pointed to the spot with City's top scorer stepping up to take the penalty. As Aguero got ready for his spot-kick, Barca midfielder Javier Mascherano pointed in the direction he thought his fellow Argentine would shoot.

